BODY.CONTENT:
Fireweed is generally considered safe for most adults when consumed moderately, for example as tea or as part of the diet. The European Medicines Agency (EMA) recognizes it as acceptable for traditional use, especially for urinary tract support.

 Nevertheless, some precautions apply:
- Pregnancy and breastfeeding;
- Use of anticoagulants (blood-thinning medications);
- Use of diuretics;
- Individual tendency to allergic reactions.

> When consumed in large amounts, possible side effects include digestive discomfort, mild sedative effects, or lowered blood pressure.

Since the metabolism of fireweed's active compounds depends on the state of the gut microbiota, individual responses may vary. It is recommended to start with small amounts.
